messages.text:
### Heroku Database
- Set up heroku
- set up database: `heroku addons:create heroku-postgresql:hobby-dev`
- set up .env file
- touch `.env` in root
- npm i dotenv -S
- add `require('dotenv').config()` to top of knexfile.js
- edit .env
- see name of project: `heroku config`
- copy the DATABASE_URL and add `?ssl=true`
- make sure your knexfile.js production.connection is set to `connection: process.env.DATABASE_URL,`
